    h1 About
    hr.line
    
    p Hello, my name is Divyanshu Tiwari, and I am a final year undergraduate student of Architecture at the Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee, India. I am primarily interested in HCI research centered around the development of new and novel interfaces that go beyond the conventional screens. I am currently looking for 
      span.bold research internship 
      | opportunities for 2022 summers.

    p For more details about me, please go through the rest of this page and the website. You can also have a look at my 
      a(href=href="../files/DivyanshuTiwari.pdf") resume
      |.

    h2 Research Interests
    p I wish to contribute to the future of 
      span.bold Human Computer Interaction 
      | by working on the development of new and novel interfaces that bring computation to the outside world, away from screens.

    h2 Experience
    ul
      li
        p I worked at the 
          span.bold Psychology Lab 
          | of IIT Roorkee under the supervision of Prof. Manish Kumar Asthana. I was responsible for developing a number of interactive virtual environments on Unity and Vizard 7. These were used to collect behavioural data of users by testing them on particular tasks. I also analysed participant's behavioural data thus collected to gain insights into their behaviour.

      li
        p I worked at 
          span.bold Razorpay 
          | as a Full-Stack Designer during the summers of 2019 where I designed and developed an 
          a(href="https://www.figma.com/file/dqH2lFZQsK2kbrXqssqPNO/Razorpay-Internship-Work?node-id=0%3A1") interactive section
          |  for their company's website with the aim of recommending product solutions in accordance with their user needs.

      li
        p I also worked at the 
          span.bold Net-Zed Lab 
          | in IIT Roorkee as a research assistant during the winters of 2018 under the supervision of 
          a(href="https://www.iitr.ac.in/departments/AR/pages/People+Rajasekhar_Elangovan.html") Prof. Elangovan Rajasekar
          | . Here I developed a 
          a(href="../projects/projects-smart-ac") prototype
          |  that automated the functioning of an AC remote control to optimise upon human comfort and energy efficiency.

